<subSubSection id="96A6078A78B7F9F2BCCFCA927003E57F" pageId="19" pageNumber="80" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="55F545B3FEEFB970E01106939895CF11" pageId="19" pageNumber="80">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E43BBC652AA3F18C0972A9CC130BBC80" pageId="19" pageNumber="80">
<taxonomicName id="B2F3ED4000969108EAF63BB79868D997" authorityName="Valdespino, G. Heringer &amp; Salino" authorityYear="2015" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella sematophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="19" pageNumber="80" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="sematophylla">
<emphasis id="FDA94A70B941E4F5305D7334FDCA1929" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="80">Selaginella sematophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of subg. 
<taxonomicName id="ABA548C0E7C8DB7DB67F42F1D7D69C90" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="(Stachygynandrum)" order="Selaginellales" pageId="19" pageNumber="80" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Stachygynandrum">
<emphasis id="7FD7E99DAF597417EA855C4B66FB5D4B" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="80">Stachygynandrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is characterized by having stems 1-branched, lateral and median leaves with hyaline margins, and idioblasts on upper surfaces of median leaves (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="33179FE3C891A2CEC0F89729E1DDF3EE" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Selaginella sematophylla Valdespino, G. Heringer &amp; Salino. A Section of upper surface of stem B Upper surface of median leaf C Section of lower surface of stem D Lower surface of lateral leaf A-D taken from paratype, Brade et al. [Beta 109] (R)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.50.4873.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/45226" pageId="19" pageNumber="80">14A, B</figureCitation>
), lower surface of lateral leaves (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1AE59DFEBA45727D7B4F9453CB0A82F6" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Selaginella sematophylla Valdespino, G. Heringer &amp; Salino. A Section of upper surface of stem B Upper surface of median leaf C Section of lower surface of stem D Lower surface of lateral leaf A-D taken from paratype, Brade et al. [Beta 109] (R)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.50.4873.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/45226" pageId="19" pageNumber="80">14C, D</figureCitation>
), and on both surfaces of sporophylls.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="29079C13734C47C2B777D8601A18CCE7" pageId="19" pageNumber="80">
In the past, specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="3F1CB0A8A2CECEABAF26A1682D349A30" authorityName="Valdespino, G. Heringer &amp; Salino" authorityYear="2015" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella sematophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="19" pageNumber="80" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="sematophylla">
<emphasis id="5E75D7495EE34E5563392F45280C9C46" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="80">Selaginella sematophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were identified as 
<taxonomicName id="3F1DEF299CB1893773DDAFEF702A7D46" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella fragillima" order="Selaginellales" pageId="19" pageNumber="80" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="fragillima">
<emphasis id="5A734955A3B97445EF920936684BF532" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="80">Selaginella fragillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4A7E12215A668E103CC8FDC6F05D8F26" authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella vestiens" order="Selaginellales" pageId="19" pageNumber="80" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="vestiens">
<emphasis id="E063B9771405DB915840C7D7AB89D891" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="80">Selaginella vestiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which see for discussion). 
<taxonomicName id="6C586C4BEAE009EF3DA8AE6EAA2861E9" authorityName="Valdespino, G. Heringer &amp; Salino" authorityYear="2015" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella sematophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="19" pageNumber="80" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="sematophylla">
<emphasis id="6AEEE77DDD6063EC82A0FADFA577865F" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="80">Selaginella sematophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="5DE5BAE8B49BB5405FE0BB0E078D120C" authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella vestiens" order="Selaginellales" pageId="19" pageNumber="80" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="vestiens">
<emphasis id="362E09E461E2EB23563BC0ABFC5A8FF6" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="80">Selaginella vestiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by cell types on leaf surfaces, median leaf apex shape, and habit, as discussed in the diagnosis.
</paragraph>
